{
  "texts": [
    "This finding highlights the important role of graph pooling in enhancing the performance of graph neural networks.",
    "• Advantages of Hierarchical Pooling: With its unique hierarchical architecture, the hierarchical pooling approach demonstrates superior performance over global pooling on multiple datasets.",
    "This advantage is mainly attributed to the fact that hierarchical pooling can capture and retain the hierarchical information of the graphs more effectively, which improves the model's ability to understand complex graph-structured data.",
    "• Applicability and selection of graph pooling methods: Although graph pooling methods have significant potential to improve model performance, their performance is still constrained by the complexity of the graph structure.",
    "Graph pooling methods do not achieve optimal performance on all datasets."
  ]
}